<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>The best&nbsp;way&nbsp;is to ask&nbsp;them&nbsp;to click on a link or on a button that takes&nbsp;them&nbsp;back to your site or your social accounts.&nbsp;Stay away from&nbsp;using phrases such as "Buy Now", which can appear as commands, it is better to&nbsp;use&nbsp;phrases&nbsp;such as "Find out more" which are&nbsp;more&nbsp;polite invitations.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:spacer {"height":"31px"} -->
<div style="height:31px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<!-- /wp:spacer -->

<!-- wp:heading {"textAlign":"center","level":5} -->
<h5 class="has-text-align-center">Use an email marketing platform</h5>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Creating a list and sending hundreds or thousands of emails manually is time-consuming and inefficient&nbsp;- this is where an email marketing platform comes in handy. They automate processes&nbsp;and&nbsp;offer&nbsp;detailed reports, customer segmentation options for sending targeted emails, and campaign management tools.&nbsp;These are essential if you want to increase the ROI of your email campaigns in an automated way.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>There are numerous email marketing platforms and tools to choose from with different features, payment plans, and different levels of ease of use.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:spacer {"height":"31px"} -->
<div style="height:31px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<!-- /wp:spacer -->

<!-- wp:heading {"level":3,"textColor":"vivid-cyan-blue"} -->
<h3 class="has-vivid-cyan-blue-color has-text-color"><a></a>Need help writing&nbsp;a&nbsp;newsletter and marketing content?</h3>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>To create truly effective and engaging newsletters,&nbsp;<a></a>ElevateOM’s&nbsp;Digital Marketing experts can help you&nbsp;engage&nbsp;your readers with&nbsp;purposeful&nbsp;and professionally written&nbsp;newslettercontent that&nbsp;will form part of your&nbsp;content marketing strategy&nbsp;and help you&nbsp;to achieve your goals.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p><a></a>Give us a call on 0800 69 06 009 or fill out a&nbsp;<a href="https://www.elevateom.com/contact/">Contact Request</a></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->"
"<!-- wp:heading {"level":4,"textColor":"vivid-cyan-blue"} -->
<h4 class="has-vivid-cyan-blue-color has-text-color">DIGITAL MARKETING STRATEGIES TO GROW YOUR BUSINESS ONLINE</h4>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>With&nbsp;a&nbsp;myriad of&nbsp;advertising&nbsp;channels&nbsp;and&nbsp;digital marketing&nbsp;tools&nbsp;on the web&nbsp;today,&nbsp;you might not think&nbsp;it&nbsp;is still&nbsp;appropriate to&nbsp;consider emails&nbsp;and newsletters&nbsp;as&nbsp;digital&nbsp;assets.&nbsp;Sadly, you’d be wrong -&nbsp;good old&nbsp;email marketing is still an&nbsp;effective communication&nbsp;channel&nbsp;if&nbsp;you follow a few simple ideas that remain&nbsp;consistent with&nbsp;the rest of&nbsp;your&nbsp;onlinemarketing strategy.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:spacer {"height":"34px"} -->
<div style="height:34px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<!-- /wp:spacer -->

<!-- wp:heading -->
<h2>What is a newsletter?</h2>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>A newsletter, which we can also call&nbsp;<em>email marketing&nbsp;</em>or&nbsp;<em>direct email</em>&nbsp;<em>marketing</em>&nbsp;is&nbsp;web&nbsp;content sent periodically via&nbsp;an email marketing&nbsp;platform which uses&nbsp;the&nbsp;contact&nbsp;informationand&nbsp;email addresses of people&nbsp;whom&nbsp;we know&nbsp;have engaged or&nbsp;are interested&nbsp;in our products and services.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>One of the&nbsp;main&nbsp;objectives&nbsp;of this form of marketing&nbsp;is to establish a relationship of trust with those who receive&nbsp;a newsletter, and thus, is a&nbsp;great tool to use for&nbsp;growing&nbsp;small and medium-sized businesses, professional&nbsp;services and&nbsp;eCommerce&nbsp;sites.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:heading {"textAlign":"center","level":4} -->
<h4 class="has-text-align-center">Getting Started With A Newsletter</h4>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:spacer {"height":"19px"} -->
<div style="height:19px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<!-- /wp:spacer -->

<!-- wp:heading {"textAlign":"center","level":5} -->
<h5 class="has-text-align-center">How to create an effective newsletter</h5>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>To make this form&nbsp;of&nbsp;communication our ally, however, we need a well-qualified database of recipients&nbsp;of&nbsp;which we have&nbsp;pre-authorisation to&nbsp;send marketing material,&nbsp;and which is preferably&nbsp;sub-divided by specific interests.&nbsp;</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Like any communication and content marketing tool, it is important that at a newsletter’s coreis a strategy, objective, valuable content to share, a tone of voice and graphics that reflects your corporate message;&nbsp;and&nbsp;above all,&nbsp;offers&nbsp;value&nbsp;to readers.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:spacer {"height":"31px"} -->
<div style="height:31px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<!-- /wp:spacer -->

<!-- wp:heading {"textAlign":"center","level":5} -->
<h5 class="has-text-align-center">Gather Contact Info</h5>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>To be able to&nbsp;effectively begin sending your customers a&nbsp;newsletter, particular attention must be paid to&nbsp;how we gather&nbsp;contact&nbsp;information.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Usually,&nbsp;at some point,&nbsp;users&nbsp;will be prompted to&nbsp;fill out a&nbsp;short&nbsp;form on&nbsp;your&nbsp;website. In some cases, this step can be encouraged by offering the user a&nbsp;discount on products or services, or a gift&nbsp;in exchange&nbsp;for their email address&nbsp;and contact info. Giving visitors a reason to&nbsp;subscribe&nbsp;to a newsletter&nbsp;is&nbsp;essential&nbsp;if you want to&nbsp;build a list of&nbsp;pre-qualified&nbsp;contacts&nbsp;to&nbsp;make this&nbsp;form of marketing&nbsp;truly effective.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:spacer {"height":"31px"} -->
<div style="height:31px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<!-- /wp:spacer -->

<!-- wp:heading {"textAlign":"center","level":5} -->
<h5 class="has-text-align-center">Create valuable newsletter content</h5>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>An effective newsletter&nbsp;should aim to&nbsp;satisfy&nbsp;a user's need and, at the same time, bring&nbsp;resultsto your marketing efforts&nbsp;– in this case, sales conversions.&nbsp;The success of sending a newsletter depends on many factors, some of which must be taken into consideration even before the drafting of the newsletter itself begins.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Firstly, define&nbsp;the&nbsp;intent and&nbsp;goal of every newsletter you write, here are some examples:</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>•&nbsp;informative&nbsp;(if you need to communicate news, new products or changes)</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>•&nbsp;to&nbsp;download content (if you are sending a lead magnet)</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>•&nbsp;to&nbsp;bring traffic to&nbsp;your blog&nbsp;(if you have written a new article and want to have it read)</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>•&nbsp;to&nbsp;obtain information (if you have prepared a questionnaire for the reader to fill out)</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>•&nbsp;to&nbsp;transform&nbsp;a&nbsp;prospect into&nbsp;a&nbsp;lead (if you want them to&nbsp;explore a new product line)</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>•&nbsp;to&nbsp;sell (if you have an eCommerce&nbsp;site)</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>•&nbsp;to&nbsp;recover an abandoned cart</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Whatever your industry and business, it is important to reach your customers through&nbsp;the use of&nbsp;quality content. Whether it's sharing news about your products or services, announcing events, presenting offers or providing solutions to particular problems&nbsp;– overall, you mustoffer something unique and valuable. Think about what differentiates your brand from others and emphasise this in your newsletter, demonstrating your value proposition.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:spacer {"height":"31px"} -->
<div style="height:31px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<!-- /wp:spacer -->

<!-- wp:heading {"textAlign":"center","level":5} -->
<h5 class="has-text-align-center">Create personalised content</h5>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Nobody likes to receive generic and impersonal&nbsp;marketing material – it’ll soon land you in their spam box. Personalised&nbsp;newsletters are much more effective because they show the reader that you have taken the time to understand their needs and that you are interested in them as an individual. A mistake that is made all too often is to focus on what you want to say, rather than what customers&nbsp;really&nbsp;want to know.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:spacer {"height":"31px"} -->
<div style="height:31px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<!-- /wp:spacer -->

<!-- wp:heading {"textAlign":"center","level":5} -->
<h5 class="has-text-align-center">Encourage a call to action</h5>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>CTAs (Call To Action) are an indispensable tool to get your readers to take action.&nbsp;Having a high email-open rate is certainly a great place to start, but the ultimate goal of a newsletter is to get results. Through the CTAs, customers can be invited to interact&nbsp;with your newsletter&nbsp;in&nbsp;ways that will lead to results.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>The best&nbsp;way&nbsp;is to ask&nbsp;them&nbsp;to click on a link or on a button that takes&nbsp;them&nbsp;back to your site or your social accounts.&nbsp;Stay away from&nbsp;using phrases such as "Buy Now", which can appear as commands, it is better to&nbsp;use&nbsp;phrases&nbsp;such as "Find out more" which are&nbsp;more&nbsp;polite invitations.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:spacer {"height":"31px"} -->
<div style="height:31px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<!-- /wp:spacer -->

<!-- wp:heading {"textAlign":"center","level":5} -->
<h5 class="has-text-align-center">Use an email marketing platform</h5>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Creating a list and sending hundreds or thousands of emails manually is time-consuming and inefficient&nbsp;- this is where an email marketing platform comes in handy. They automate processes&nbsp;and&nbsp;offer&nbsp;detailed reports, customer segmentation options for sending targeted emails, and campaign management tools.&nbsp;These are essential if you want to increase the ROI of your email campaigns in an automated way.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>There are numerous email marketing platforms and tools to choose from with different features, payment plans, and different levels of ease of use.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:spacer {"height":"31px"} -->
<div style="height:31px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<!-- /wp:spacer -->

