 	<li class="x_MsoNormal">Payments for WebCare products are non-refundable and non-transferable.</li>
 	<li class="x_MsoNormal">As part of all WebCare packages you receive DDoS protection. This is provided via a third party, Cloudflare Inc. Our DDoS protection is intended to provide an extra security layer to your website in the event of a DDoS attack against your website or services. If your services are interrupted or taken offline due to a DDoS attack Elevate Online marketing Ltd. will endeavour to restore these services ASAP. We cannot be held liable financially or otherwise for a DDoS attack.</li>
 	<li class="x_MsoNormal">Elevate Online Marketing Ltd. do not take any responsibility for a client’s website rank on search engines. This also includes any potential website downtime that can occur. When updating, changing, creating and hosting a client’s website, there could be a change in the websites search engine ranking.</li>
</ol>
<strong>Domain Names and Links</strong>
<ol>
 	<li>If required, a domain name will be registered by Elevate Online Marketing Ltd. on behalf of the client once we have received payment in full. Although the domain name is registered to Elevate Online marketing Ltd., the client is the legal owner of the domain and if they request to have details changed or the domain transferred elsewhere, we will do this within a reasonable timeframe.</li>
 	<li>Elevate Online marketing Ltd. provides links or references to our client’s websites solely for the convenience of prospective customers and intends that the links it provides be current and accurate but does not guarantee or warrant that such links will point to the intended client site at all times.</li>
 	<li>We place a small text link on the footer of our client’s website that simply states the website was designed by Elevate Online Marketing Ltd. and links to our company website. This link can be removed, if required.</li>
</ol>
<strong>Video Services</strong>
<ol>
 	<li>Elevate Online marketing Ltd. will create a video as per the details set out in your invoice. The length of the video will be detailed in the invoice.</li>
 	<li>Payment for the video will be 100% upfront.</li>
 	<li>Elevate Online Marketing Ltd. may use pre-created video, animation, graphics or images as part of your video. As the client you will not own the copyright to this content.</li>
 	<li>We offer up to 5 revisions to video whilst it is being created. Once you have signed off the video and agreed via email that it is complete, we will charge for additional changes required.</li>
 	<li>If your video contains ‘voice over’ then we may use voice over software to produce the voice over. This will therefore be a simulated human voice produced by the software.</li>
 	<li>We will upload your video to the Elevate Online Marketing Ltd. YouTube channel. You can use this video for use digitally, such as your website.</li>
</ol>
<strong>Image Services</strong>
<ol>
 	<li>Elevate Online marketing Ltd. will create select and provide image options to the client to approve. Images are selected from a number of resource libraries and selected based on the site content, business type and general image look.</li>
 	<li>Payment for the service will be 100% upfront.</li>
 	<li>We offer up to 5 revisions to your initial image selection whilst the service is being delivered. Once you have agreed to the image selection by phone or email the service will be marked as complete. We will charge for additional changes if requested after this point.</li>
 	<li>We will upload your selected images to your website once approved.</li>
</ol>"


"<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>In nearly every&nbsp;business&nbsp;department, monthly and/or yearly reports form among the most important tools for&nbsp;assessing the performance of past&nbsp;strategies and campaigns&nbsp;with which to&nbsp;implement&nbsp;new ideas and make&nbsp;future&nbsp;business&nbsp;decisions.&nbsp;</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Likewise, digital marketing reports should form a fundamental aspect of your online marketing activities. They should be used to monitor advertising performance and ROI (Return On Investment), help you make sensible tweaks and changes to user experience and help understand the impact that your communication channels are having on your business.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Let's&nbsp;take a look at a few advantages&nbsp;of&nbsp;monthly&nbsp;digital&nbsp;marketing reporting.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:spacer {"height":"27px"} -->
<div style="height:27px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<!-- /wp:spacer -->

<!-- wp:heading {"level":4} -->
<h4>Assess&nbsp;KPIs&nbsp;and Objectives</h4>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>The analysis of KPIs, or&nbsp;<em>Key Performance Indicators</em>, allows you to understand the performance of a marketing&nbsp;strategy&nbsp;with respect to the objectives you set for yourself and allows you to identify areas for improvement.&nbsp;It&nbsp;also&nbsp;allows you to fine-tune and&nbsp;act&nbsp;to&nbsp;correct&nbsp;issues&nbsp;as soon as possible.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p><strong>Here are just some of the main KPIs in Digital Marketing:</strong></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>•&nbsp;Page visits and mobile&nbsp;traffic.&nbsp;</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>•&nbsp;Conversion rates.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>•&nbsp;CPC or the cost per click</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>•&nbsp;CPL or the cost per lead</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>•&nbsp;CPA or the cost per acquisition</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>•&nbsp;ROI or the return on investment</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>KPIs are essential to understanding&nbsp;whether&nbsp;what you are doing&nbsp;is reaping&nbsp;the desired results or not&nbsp;and&nbsp;digital&nbsp;marketing&nbsp;reporting&nbsp;should,&nbsp;therefore,&nbsp;be drawn up&nbsp;at least&nbsp;monthly to evaluate&nbsp;whether KPIs&nbsp;align with&nbsp;the efforts and spending&nbsp;of&nbsp;various&nbsp;digital marketing&nbsp;campaigns.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:spacer {"height":"27px"} -->
<div style="height:27px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<!-- /wp:spacer -->

<!-- wp:heading {"level":4} -->
<h4>Get an overview of all&nbsp;marketing channels</h4>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>The best approach to achieving your marketing objectives is with a multi-channel marketing plan&nbsp;that enables you to&nbsp;interact and engage with your audience successfully regardless of&nbsp;where they are on the internet.&nbsp;</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>However, because&nbsp;data&nbsp;is often&nbsp;spread across several marketing platforms, multi-channel strategies can be challenging to administer. This issue is lessened by monthly marketing reporting, which combines metrics from several sources&nbsp;and collates&nbsp;them&nbsp;into a single, consolidated report. This&nbsp;means&nbsp;that you can evaluate the impact each channel has on the consumer experience&nbsp;and its&nbsp;effectiveness.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Digital marketing&nbsp;reports&nbsp;are a fundamental part of&nbsp;your&nbsp;marketing activities&nbsp;and&nbsp;they&nbsp;shouldbe&nbsp;collated&nbsp;and available&nbsp;regularly -&nbsp;only&nbsp;then&nbsp;can you make&nbsp;concrete&nbsp;decisions&nbsp;on&nbsp;futureadvertising and communication&nbsp;activities.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:spacer {"height":"27px"} -->
<div style="height:27px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<!-- /wp:spacer -->

<!-- wp:heading {"level":4} -->
<h4>Evaluate your marketing team’s efforts</h4>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>A good digital marketing report&nbsp;also aims to&nbsp;highlight the&nbsp;efforts&nbsp;of&nbsp;your digital&nbsp;marketing department&nbsp;or digital marketing agency&nbsp;and shows why they are a good investment&nbsp;(or not).&nbsp;</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>The data obtained from your website, social media and online advertising is essential so that it may become a source of ideas and information on how to improve business processes. It also helps you spot any communication and collaboration gaps between teams so that you can put in place better procedures that promote a more cohesive marketing strategy. </p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:spacer {"height":"27px"} -->
<div style="height:27px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<!-- /wp:spacer -->

