"<!-- wp:heading {"level":4} -->
<h4>Black Friday Digital Marketing Strategies &amp; Tips</h4>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>The busiest online shopping weekend of the year is upon us – the Black Friday &amp; Cyber Monday rush is among the most important time of the year for online stores. eCommerce and online businesses only have a short window of time to entice shoppers to take advantage of products and great offers from <em>their</em> websites among a dizzying array of competitors and flash deals.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>To do this successfully, however, it is necessary, as always, to set up an effective digital marketing strategy for maximising your advertising campaigns in terms of sales and ROAS (Return On Advertising Spend).</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Let's have a look at some eCommerce strategies for Black Friday and Cyber Monday, 2022.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:heading {"textAlign":"center","level":4} -->
<h4 class="has-text-align-center">Plan Ahead</h4>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Not millions, but billions of promotional emails are sent in the run-up to Black Friday. This is the period when your emails will have to compete with many other brands and cut through the noise to get noticed. To be able to capture the attention of your potential customers you will need to mobilise ahead of time and plan carefully.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph {"align":"center"} -->
<p class="has-text-align-center"><em><strong>“Many retailers kick off their Black Friday sales promotion as early as the end of October, while others start promotions in early November.”</strong></em></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Pre-Black Friday is a crucial part of building an audience that is warmed up and prepared to buy when the time comes. Concentrate on those who are familiar with you, follow you, have seen your items, and have engaged with them. At the same time, it is also advisable to carry out a campaign on social networks or increase your ad budget to attract new potential buyers ahead of Black Friday.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Cold selling can be an added expense, especially for businesses with modest budgets. If you want to get noticed, the biggest piece of advice is to act early.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:heading {"textAlign":"center","level":4} -->
<h4 class="has-text-align-center">Invest In Paid Search And Google Ads</h4>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Paid advertising campaigns are an effective eCommerce marketing strategy you can use to attract more customers this Black Friday.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>According to a recent study, almost half of all Black Friday deals are now decided by paid search advertising.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>While organic traffic is the best way to rank high on Google and other search engine results pages&nbsp;(SERPs), paid ads can be a game-changer for Black Friday and Cyber Monday eCommerce marketing.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Running PPC <em>(Pay Per Click)</em> ads in the days leading up to Black Friday weekend is an excellent marketing tool for increasing online traffic.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:heading {"textAlign":"center","level":4} -->
<h4 class="has-text-align-center">Optimise your content and offers</h4>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>The same goes for the use of keywords in your content. By relying on tools like Google Keyword Planners and Google Trends you can find the keywords to use in the descriptions and content of your site to maximise both the quality and quantity of your traffic.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p><strong>Content optimisation focuses on addressing issues in the following:</strong></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:list -->
<ul><li>Internal links</li><li>Keywords</li><li>Featured snippets</li><li>URLs</li><li>Readability</li></ul>
<!-- /wp:list -->

<!-- wp:heading {"textAlign":"center","level":4} -->
<h4 class="has-text-align-center">Send an E-Mail With Special Discounts</h4>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Although&nbsp;emails&nbsp;are one of the oldest forms of digital marketing, they should still be seen as valid and effective allies. Equally, everyone loves a special offer!</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Sending your contact list an email promising them a special discount will increase the anticipation when Black Friday arrives and gives them a reason to go and explore your products on offer in the hope of bagging a great deal.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Don't make discounts impossible and torturous to understand, however. Try to keep it simple, and be direct and immediate with your wording.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p><strong>Discover the best ideas and tips to </strong><a href="a"><strong>create a perfect newsletter</strong></a><strong> for Black Friday in our blog post</strong></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

